<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2020-03-23</DATELINE><TITLE>Emergency Management of the Prevention and Control of Novel Coronavirus Pneumonia in Specialized Branches of Hospital</TITLE><BODY>Abstract In December 2019, an epidemic of novel coronavirus pneumonia (NCP) broke out in Wuhan, Hubei Province. The outbreak was severe and coincided with the Spring Festival travel season. On January 15, 2020, the West China Hospital of Sichuan University, a large hospital in China, held a seminar on prevention and control in accordance with the requirements of the National Health Commission on Prevention and Control. On January 16, the emergency plan for the prevention and treatment of NCP in West China Hospital of Sichuan University was formulated for the first time.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>